                <head>315. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Telegram 2404 to Vienna, March 18, authorized Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> to exchange notes with the Austrian
                    Government on settlement of claims under Article 26 of the Austrian State
                    Treaty, which provided for compensation of political persecutees. (Department of
                    State, Central Files, 263.0041–A/3–1359) Delays by the British and French, who
                    concluded similar agreements, postponed the exchange until May 1959. For text of
                    the treaty, which entered into force on May 22, see 10 UST 1158.</p>
            </div>
